b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. RankMath is best suited for WordPress users, bloggers, small business sites, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Yoast SEO, meanwhile, shines for WordPress beginners, bloggers, small websites, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2018, RankMath describes itself as \"Advanced WordPress SEO plugin with AI-powered content optimization.\" Yoast SEO, established in 2010, positions itself as \"The most popular WordPress SEO plugin for on-page optimization.\" With 8 years between them, Yoast SEO brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while RankMath offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **RankMath** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more features (6 vs 2), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Yoast SEO is a poor choice — far from it. Yoast SEO excels in its own right, particularly for WordPress beginners and bloggers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value generous free version with advanced features, go with RankMath. If industry standard wordpress seo plugin matters more to you, Yoast SEO is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
